            <!-- articles -->
            <div class="text">
                <p>
                    Are you curious to learn business and technology?
                </p>
                <p>Hi, my name is Jerry and I majored in business in my uni year, focusing on Finance. Having worked
                    2 years
                    in strategic consulting, then I moved on
                    to one of the fortune 500 companies to learn the commercial side of things. While in the
                    business world,
                    for my curiosity in technology,
                    I self-taught my self web development technology. I did not plan out the self-taught journey as
                    such but
                    due to Covid19, I
                    have to postpone my plan of further studies in computer science. So I started self-learning
                    while
                    WFH...After about 1 year, I have the modules that
                    are offered by most bootcamps, while refering to their course contents.
                </p>

                <p>Why curiosity as the centre piece of this blog? During my journey of learning business and tech,
                    I
                    released
                    curiosity is a form of super energy that lies dormant within you and me. With this realization,
                    I was
                    able harness this untapped
                    energy to accelerate my learning. In this blog, I will share with you all about this, while
                    specifically
                    focusing on business and technology because
                    both has become increasingly connected nowadays.
                </p>

                <h2>
                    What curiosity is not?
                </h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Curiosity is not about absorbing large amount of information. In this era, we are actually
                        inundated
                        with so much information to the
                        point of information fatigue. Our brain is to create ideas, not to memorize information.
                    </li>
                </ol>

               

                <div class="blogposts">

                    <!-- pass database data into the html -->
                    <% for(var i=0; i<blogposts.length; i++) { %>
                        <a href="/post/<%= blogposts[i]._id %>">
                            <h2 class="title">
                                <%= blogposts[i].title %>
                            </h2>

                            <h3 class="body">
                                <%- blogposts[i].body.split('</p>')[0] + '...'+ '</p>' %>
                            </h3>
                        </a>
                        <p class="postedBy">Posted by Jerry
                            on <%= blogposts[i].datePosted.toDateString() %>
                        </p>
                        <% } %>

                </div>

            </div>

            <!-- footer -->
            <%- include('layouts/footer'); -%>


        </div>
        <%- include('layouts/script'); -%>

    </body>

</html>